es NOT grow on a bush?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"blueberry-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Blueberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blueberry-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Gooseberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blueberry-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Raspberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blueberry-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Strawberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"blueberry-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Strawberry grows on the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Strawberry is the odd one out — it grows on the ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Blueberries turn your tongue blue — check after eating one!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry\",\"name\":\"Raspberry\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/raspberry.webp\",\"category\":\"berry\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"red\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am made up of lots of tiny round drupelets!\",\"highlightWord\":\"drupelets\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on tall, thorny canes in the garden!\",\"highlightWord\":\"thorny\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to roses — we are in the same family!\",\"highlightWord\":\"roses\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of fibre and vitamin C!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fibre\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"raspberry-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"raspberry-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4169E1\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"raspberry-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am red!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am actually red!\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"raspberry-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"raspberry-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow on a thorny bush!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow on a thorny bush!\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Raspberries are related to roses\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"raspberry-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"raspberry-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! We share the same plant family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, raspberries and roses are in the same family!\"},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT red?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"raspberry-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Strawberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Raspberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Blueberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"raspberry-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Cranberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"raspberry-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Blueberry is blue, not red!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Blueberry is the odd one out — it is blue!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Each raspberry is made of around 100 tiny individual fruits called drupelets!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry\",\"name\":\"Blackberry\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/blackberry.webp\",\"category\":\"berry\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"black\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I start red, then turn deep purple-black when ripe!\",\"highlightWord\":\"ripe\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on thorny canes called brambles!\",\"highlightWord\":\"brambles\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to raspberries and roses!\",\"highlightWord\":\"raspberries\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with vitamin C and antioxidants!\",\"highlightWord\":\"antioxidants\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"blackberry-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I when ripe?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"blackberry-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#1a1a2e\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"blackberry-q1-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am dark purple-black!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am dark purple-black when ripe!\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"blackberry-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"blackberry-q2-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow on a thorny bush!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow on thorny bramble bushes!\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Blackberries are green when unripe\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"blackberry-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"blackberry-q3-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I am red when unripe, not green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am red when unripe, then turn black when ripe!\"},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow on a thorny bush?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"blackberry-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Blackberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Raspberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Blueberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"blackberry-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Gooseberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"blackberry-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Blueberry bushes do not have thorns!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Blueberry is the odd one out — its bush has no thorns!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Wild blackberries have been eaten by humans since prehistoric times!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"cranberry\",\"name\":\"Cranberry\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/cranberry.webp\",\"category\":\"berry\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"red\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"North America\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am very tart and sour — not sweet at all!\",\"highlightWord\":\"tart\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on low vines in boggy, flooded fields!\",\"highlightWord\":\"boggy\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"Farmers flood my fields to harvest me — I float on water!\",\"highlightWord\":\"float\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I help keep urinary tract infections away!\",\"highlightWord\":\"infections\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"cranberry-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cranberry-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cranberry-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cranberry-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4169E1\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cranberry-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am deep red!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am deep red!\"},{\"id\":\"cranberry-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cranberry-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\