\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pomegranate-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I can have up to 1,000 seeds inside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I can have between 200 and 1,400 seeds inside!\"},{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT have edible seeds?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Pomegranate\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Strawberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Avocado\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pomegranate-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Kiwi\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pomegranate-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Avocado has a large stone, not edible seeds!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Avocado is the odd one out — its stone is not eaten!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Ancient Greeks believed pomegranates had exactly 613 seeds — one for each commandment!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"carrot\",\"name\":\"Carrot\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/carrot.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"orange\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Afghanistan\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a bright orange root vegetable!\",\"highlightWord\":\"orange\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground with feathery green leaves above!\",\"highlightWord\":\"underground\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of beta-carotene which helps your eyesight!\",\"highlightWord\":\"beta-carotene\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"Carrots were originally purple before orange ones were bred!\",\"highlightWord\":\"purple\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"carrot-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"carrot-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#9B59B6\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0077B6\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"carrot-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am orange!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am actually orange!\"},{\"id\":\"carrot-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"carrot-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"carrot-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"carrot-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"carrot-q2-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground!\"},{\"id\":\"carrot-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Carrots help you see in the dark\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"carrot-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"carrot-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! My vitamin A helps eye health!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, my beta-carotene does support good eye health!\"},{\"id\":\"carrot-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a root vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"carrot-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Beetroot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"carrot-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Parsnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"carrot-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Broccoli is not a root vegetable!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Broccoli is the odd one out — it grows above ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Original carrots were purple — orange carrots were bred in the Netherlands!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"potato\",\"name\":\"Potato\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/potato.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"yellow\",\"brown\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"South America\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a starchy tuber that grows underground!\",\"highlightWord\":\"tuber\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I originally came from the Andes mountains in South America!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Andes\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am the world's most eaten vegetable!\",\"highlightWord\":\"eaten\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of carbohydrates and vitamin B6 for energy!\",\"highlightWord\":\"carbohydrates\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"potato-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"potato-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4169E1\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"potato-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My skin is brown!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! My skin is usually brown!\"},{\"id\":\"potato-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"potato-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"potato-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"potato-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"potato-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground!\"},{\"id\":\"potato-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Potatoes are the most widely eaten vegetable in the world\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"potato-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"potato-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I am eaten all over the world!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am the most widely eaten vegetable on Earth!\"},{\"id\":\"potato-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow underground?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"potato-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Potato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Tomato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"potato-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Beetroot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"potato-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Tomato grows above ground on a vine!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Tomato is the odd one out — it grows above ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"The potato was the first vegetable grown in space — by NASA in 1995!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"beetroot\",\"name\":\"Beetroot\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/beetroot.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"red\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am deep red and will stain your fingers pink!\",\"highlightWord\":\"stain\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground with leafy greens above!\",\"highlightWord\":\"leafy\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"My greens are also edible — two veggies in one!\",\"highlightWord\":\"greens\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of folate and nitrates for a healthy heart!\",\"highlightWord\":\"nitrates\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"beetroot-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"beetroot-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"beetroot-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"beetro