eet-potato-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweet-potato-q3-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! We are from completely different plant families!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, sweet potatoes are not closely related to regular potatoes!\"},{\"id\":\"sweet-potato-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow underground?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"sweet-potato-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Sweet Potato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweet-potato-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweet-potato-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Pumpkin\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweet-potato-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Parsnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweet-potato-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Pumpkin grows on a vine on the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Pumpkin is the odd one out — it grows on the ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Sweet potatoes were carried into space by astronauts as an important food source!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"turnip\",\"name\":\"Turnip\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/turnip.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am white and purple with a peppery taste!\",\"highlightWord\":\"peppery\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground in cool autumn and winter weather!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cool\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to cabbage, broccoli, and kale!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cabbage\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am low in calories and high in vitamin C!\",\"highlightWord\":\"calories\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"turnip-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my top?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"turnip-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#6A0DAD\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4169E1\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"turnip-q1-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My top is purple!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! My top is purple and my bottom is white!\"},{\"id\":\"turnip-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"turnip-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"turnip-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"turnip-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"turnip-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground!\"},{\"id\":\"turnip-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Turnips are related to broccoli and cabbage\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"turnip-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"turnip-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! We are all in the brassica family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, turnips, broccoli, and cabbage are all brassicas!\"},{\"id\":\"turnip-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a brassica vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"turnip-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Turnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Kale\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"turnip-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Cabbage\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"turnip-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Carrot is not a brassica!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Carrot is the odd one out — it is not a brassica!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Before pumpkins, people in Ireland carved turnips for Halloween!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"radish\",\"name\":\"Radish\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/radish.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"red\",\"white\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Asia\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am small, round, and bright red with a white inside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"round\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow very fast — ready to eat in just 3 weeks!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fast\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I have a spicy, peppery crunch when you bite me!\",\"highlightWord\":\"spicy\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am low in calories and high in vitamin C!\",\"highlightWord\":\"low\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"radish-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"radish-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4169E1\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"radish-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My skin is red!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! My skin is red with white flesh inside!\"},{\"id\":\"radish-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"radish-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"radish-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"radish-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"radish-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground!\"},{\"id\":\"radish-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Radishes are one of the fastest vegetables to grow\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"radish-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"radish-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I can be ready in just 3-4 weeks!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am one of the fastest vegetables — ready in just weeks!\"},{\"id\":\"radish-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT spicy?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"radish-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Radish\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Horseradish\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"radish-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Wasabi\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"radish-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Carrot is sweet, not spicy!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Carrot is the odd one out — it is sweet, not spicy!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"In Mexico there is a festival called Night of the Radishes where people carve radish sculptures!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip\",\"name\":\"Parsnip\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/parsnip.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"cream\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I look like a white carrot and taste sweet and nutty!\",\"highlightWord\":\"nutty\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground and get sweeter after a frost!\",\"highlightWord\":\"frost\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to carrots and parsley — we are all in the same family!\",\"highlightWord\":\"parsley\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of fibre and folate for a healthy body!\",\"highlightWord\":\"folate\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"parsnip-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"parsnip-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#F5F5DC\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"parsnip-q1-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am cream-white!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am cream-white in colour!\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"parsnip-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"parsnip-q2-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground!\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Parsnips get sweeter after cold winter frosts\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"parsnip-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"parsnip-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! Frost turns my starch into sugar!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, frost converts my starch to sugar, making me sweeter!\"},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT cream or white?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"parsnip-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Parsnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Turnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Beetroot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"parsnip-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Celeriac\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"parsnip-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Beetroot is deep red, not white!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Beetroot is the odd one out — it is deep red!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Before sugar was widely available, parsnips were used to sweeten cakes and jam!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"ginger\",\"name\":\"Ginger\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/ginger.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"root\",\"colours\":[\"brown\",\"yellow\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Southeast Asia\",\"season\":\"all-year\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a knobbly root with a spicy, warming flavour!\",\"highlightWord\":\"knobbly\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground in tropical, humid climates!\",\"highlightWord\":\"humid\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I have been used in cooking and medicine for over 5,000 years!\",\"highlightWord\":\"medicine\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I help settle upset stomachs and fight nausea!\",\"highlightWord\":\"nausea\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"ginger-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"ginger-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"ginger-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My skin is brown!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! My skin is light brown!\"},{\"id\":\"ginger-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"ginger-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"ginger-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"ginger-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"ginger-q2-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am a root that grows underground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow underground — I am a root!\"},{\"id\":\"ginger-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Ginger can help with feeling sick\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"ginger-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"ginger-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! Ginger is a well-known remedy for nausea!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, ginger is widely used to help settle upset stomachs!\"},{\"id\":\"ginger-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a root spice?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"ginger-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Ginger\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Turmeric\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Horseradish\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"ginger-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Basil\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"ginger-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Basil is a leafy herb, not a root spice!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Basil is the odd one out — it is a leafy herb!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Ginger is related to turmeric and cardamom — all spicy tropical roots!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"spinach\",\"name\":\"Spinach\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/spinach.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Persia\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a dark leafy green full of goodness!\",\"highlightWord\":\"leafy\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow low to the ground in cool weather!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cool\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I first came from ancient Persia, now called Iran!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Persia\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with iron, calcium, and vitamin K!\",\"highlightWord\":\"iron\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"spinach-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spinach-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spinach-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am dark green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am dark green!\"},{\"id\":\"spinach-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spinach-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"spinach-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"spinach-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spinach-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow close to the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow close to the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"spinach-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Spinach is a good source of iron\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spinach-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spinach-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I am famous for my iron content!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am a great source of iron!\"},{\"id\":\"spinach-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a leafy green vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spinach-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Spinach\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Kale\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Lettuce\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spinach-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Beetroot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spinach-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Beetroot is a root vegetable!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Beetroot is the odd one out — it is a root, not a leaf!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Popeye the Sailor ate spinach for strength — and the iron really does help muscles!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce\",\"name\":\"Lettuce\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/lettuce.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Middle East\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a crispy green leafy vegetable!\",\"highlightWord\":\"crispy\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow in a rosette of leaves close to the ground!\",\"highlightWord\":\"rosette\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am over 4,000 years old — ancient Egyptians grew me!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Egyptians\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am mostly water — I keep you hydrated!\",\"highlightWord\":\"hydrated\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"lettuce-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lettuce-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#9B59B6\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lettuce-q1-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am green!\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lettuce-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lettuce-q2-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow close to the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow close to the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Lettuce is mostly made of water\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lettuce-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lettuce-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I am about 95% water!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, lettuce is about 95% water!\"},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one do you NOT find in a salad?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lettuce-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Lettuce\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Spinach\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Rocket\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lettuce-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Potato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lettuce-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Potato is usually cooked, not eaten raw in salads!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Potato is the odd one out — it is usually cooked first!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Ancient Egyptians used lettuce in religious ceremonies and offerings!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"kale\",\"name\":\"Kale\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/kale.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a dark, curly green — one of the most nutritious vegetables!\",\"highlightWord\":\"curly\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow upright with thick, ruffled leaves!\",\"highlightWord\":\"ruffled\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to broccoli, cabbage, and Brussels sprouts!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Brussels\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with vitamins K, A, and C — a true superfood!\",\"highlightWord\":\"superfood\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"kale-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"kale-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"kale-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am dark green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am dark green!\"},{\"id\":\"kale-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"kale-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"kale-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"kale-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"kale-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow upright from the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow upright from the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"kale-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Kale is related to broccoli and cabbage\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"kale-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"kale-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! We are all in the brassica family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, kale, broccoli, and cabbage are all brassicas!\"},{\"id\":\"kale-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a brassica?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"kale-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Kale\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Cabbage\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Spinach\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"kale-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"kale-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Spinach is not a brassica!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Spinach is the odd one out — it is not a brassica!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Kale was one of the most common green vegetables in Europe until the Middle Ages!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage\",\"name\":\"Cabbage\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/cabbage.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"red\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a round, dense ball of tightly packed leaves!\",\"highlightWord\":\"dense\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I can be green, red, or purple on the outside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"purple\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to broccoli, cauliflower, and kale!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cauliflower\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of vitamin C and fibre for good digestion!\",\"highlightWord\":\"digestion\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"cabbage-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour can I be?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cabbage-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cabbage-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I can be green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I can be green, red, or purple!\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cabbage-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cabbage-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow close to the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I grow close to the ground on a stout stem!\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Cabbage can be red or purple as well as green\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cabbage-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cabbage-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I come in green, red, and purple varieties!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I do come in red and purple varieties too!\"},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT made from cabbage?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cabbage-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Coleslaw\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Sauerkraut\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Hummus\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cabbage-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Kimchi\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cabbage-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Hummus is made from chickpeas, not cabbage!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Hummus is the odd one out — it is made from chickpeas!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Sauerkraut is made by fermenting cabbage — and it lasts for months!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"watercress\",\"name\":\"Watercress\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/watercress.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Europe\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I grow in and around streams and flowing water!\",\"highlightWord\":\"streams\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I have a peppery, spicy taste for a small leaf!\",\"highlightWord\":\"peppery\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am one of the oldest known leaf vegetables eaten by humans!\",\"highlightWord\":\"oldest\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am exceptionally rich in vitamins K, C, and calcium!\",\"highlightWord\":\"calcium\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"watercress-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"watercress-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"watercress-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am bright green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am bright green!\"},{\"id\":\"watercress-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"watercress-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"watercress-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"watercress-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"watercress-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow in shallow water and on the ground beside streams!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I grow in and alongside streams and shallow water!\"},{\"id\":\"watercress-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Watercress grows in and around water\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"watercress-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"watercress-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I love growing in cool flowing water!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I do grow in and around streams and water!\"},{\"id\":\"watercress-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT have a peppery taste?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"watercress-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Watercress\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Rocket\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Radish\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"watercress-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Lettuce\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"watercress-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Lettuce is mild, not peppery!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Lettuce is the odd one out — it has a mild, not peppery taste!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Watercress was prescribed by the ancient Greek doctor Hippocrates as medicine!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"rocket\",\"name\":\"Rocket\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/rocket.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"leafy\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I have a sharp, peppery bite — I am not mild like lettuce!\",\"highlightWord\":\"peppery\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow quickly from seed in just a few weeks!\",\"highlightWord\":\"quickly\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"In Italy I am called rucola and I am loved in pizza and pasta!\",\"highlightWord\":\"rucola\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am rich in vitamin K and folate for healthy blood!\",\"highlightWord\":\"blood\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"rocket-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"rocket-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"rocket-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am green!\"},{\"id\":\"rocket-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"rocket-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"rocket-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"rocket-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"rocket-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow close to the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I grow close to the ground from seed!\"},{\"id\":\"rocket-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Rocket tastes mild and sweet like lettuce\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"rocket-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"rocket-q3-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I have a sharp, peppery bite!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I have a strong peppery taste — not mild like lettuce!\"},{\"id\":\"rocket-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is also known as \\\"arugula\\\"?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"rocket-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Spinach\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Kale\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Rocket\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"rocket-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Lettuce\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"rocket-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Rocket is called arugula in America!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Rocket is the odd one out — it is called arugula in America!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Rocket is called arugula in the USA and rucola in Italy — three names, one plant!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"peas\",\"name\":\"Peas\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/peas.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"legume\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"Middle East\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am tiny, round, and bright green — sweet and delicious!\",\"highlightWord\":\"tiny\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow in pods on climbing vines!\",\"highlightWord\":\"pods\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I have been eaten for over 10,000 years — one of the oldest crops!\",\"highlightWord\":\"10,000\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of protein and vitamins B and C!\",\"highlightWord\":\"protein\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"peas-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"peas-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF8C00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"peas-q1-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am bright green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am bright green!\"},{\"id\":\"peas-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"peas-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"peas-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"peas-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"peas-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow in pods on climbing vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow in pods on climbing vines!\"},{\"id\":\"peas-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Peas grow inside pods\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"peas-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"peas-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I grow inside long green pods!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I do grow inside pods on the vine!\"},{\"id\":\"peas-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a legume?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"peas-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Peas\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Lentils\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"peas-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broad Beans\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"peas-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Carrot is a root vegetable, not a legume!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Carrot is the odd one out — it is a root, not a legume!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Gregor Mendel discovered the laws of genetics by experimenting on pea plants!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans\",\"name\":\"Green Beans\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/green-beans.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"legume\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"South America\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a long, thin green pod eaten whole!\",\"highlightWord\":\"whole\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on climbing vines or compact bush plants!\",\"highlightWord\":\"climbing\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I originally came from Central and South America!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Central\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am a good source of vitamins C and K and folate!\",\"highlightWord\":\"folate\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"green-beans-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"green-beans-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#9B59B6\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"green-beans-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am green!\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"green-beans-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"green-beans-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow on vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow on climbing vines!\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Green beans are also called French beans\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"green-beans-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"green-beans-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! French beans is another name for me!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am also known as French beans or string beans!\"},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT eaten as a whole pod?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"green-beans-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Green Beans\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Mangetout\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Broad Beans\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"green-beans-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Sugar Snap Peas\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"green-beans-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Broad beans are shelled, not eaten as whole pods!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Broad Beans are the odd one out — you shell them before eating!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Green beans were brought to Europe by Christopher Columbus after his voyages to America!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans\",\"name\":\"Broad Beans\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/broad-beans.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"legume\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"Middle East\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I grow in big, thick, fuzzy pods — you shell me before eating!\",\"highlightWord\":\"shell\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on tall, upright plants in cool spring weather!\",\"highlightWord\":\"upright\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am one of the oldest crops — grown for over 8,000 years!\",\"highlightWord\":\"8,000\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am high in protein and iron — great for vegetarians!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vegetarians\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I inside my pod?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4CAF50\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broad-beans-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am green inside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I am green inside my pod!\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broad-beans-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow on tall vine-like plants!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I actually grow on tall upright plants like vines!\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"You eat broad beans inside their thick pods\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broad-beans-q3-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! You shell me out of the pod before eating!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, you shell me out of the thick pod to eat the beans inside!\"},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one do you NOT need to shell before eating?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Broad Beans\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Peas\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Green Beans\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broad-beans-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Lentils\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broad-beans-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Green beans are eaten whole — no shelling needed!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Green Beans are the odd one out — you eat the whole pod!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Broad beans are mentioned in writings from ancient Egypt, Greece, and Rome!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"lentils\",\"name\":\"Lentils\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/lentils.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"legume\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"red\",\"brown\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Middle East\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I come in red, green, and brown varieties!\",\"highlightWord\":\"varieties\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I grow in small pods on low bushy plants!\",\"highlightWord\":\"bushy\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am one of the first crops ever grown by humans — 10,000 years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"first\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with protein, iron, and fibre — a superfood for vegetarians!\",\"highlightWord\":\"superfood\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"lentils-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour can I be?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lentils-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#E63946\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0077B6\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lentils-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I can be red!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Nearly! I come in red, green, and brown varieties!\"},{\"id\":\"lentils-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lentils-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"lentils-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"lentils-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lentils-q2-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I grow on low bushy plants close to the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"No, I grow on low bushy plants close to the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"lentils-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Lentils are a good source of protein\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lentils-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lentils-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! I am one of the best plant sources of protein!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am one of the best plant sources of protein!\"},{\"id\":\"lentils-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a legume?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"lentils-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Lentils\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Chickpeas\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Potato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"lentils-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Peas\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"lentils-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Potato is a root vegetable, not a legume!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Hmm, Potato is the odd one out — it is a root vegetable!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Lentils were found in Egyptian tombs — they were buried with pharaohs as food for the afterlife!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"onion\",\"name\":\"Onion\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/onion.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"allium\",\"colours\":[\"brown\",\"white\",\"red\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Central Asia\",\"season\":\"all-year\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I can make you cry when you cut me — sorry!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cry\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow underground as a round layered bulb!\",\"highlightWord\":\"bulb\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"People have eaten me for over 5,000 years!\",\"highlightWord\":\"5,000\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I can be white, red, brown or purple!\",\"highlightWord\":\"purple\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"onion-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin most often?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"onion-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#00FF00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"onion-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Onion skins are often brown or papery!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Onion skins are usually brown, white or red!\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"onion-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"onion-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow underground as a bulb!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow underground as a bulb!\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Cutting me can make your eyes water. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"onion-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"onion-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I release a gas that makes eyes water!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, cutting onions does make eyes water!\"},{\"id\":\"onion-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow underground?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"onion-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Onion\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Garlic\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"onion-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"onion-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Broccoli grows above ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Broccoli is the odd one — it grows above ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Onions were so valuable in the Middle Ages that people used them to pay rent!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"garlic\",\"name\":\"Garlic\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/garlic.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"allium\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"cream\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Central Asia\",\"season\":\"all-year\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am made up of many little cloves inside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cloves\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I have been used as medicine for thousands of years!\",\"highlightWord\":\"medicine\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"My strong smell comes from a chemical called allicin!\",\"highlightWord\":\"allicin\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"I originally grew wild in Central Asia!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Asia\",\"factType\":\"origin\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"garlic-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I on the outside?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"garlic-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#F5F5DC\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#32CD32\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFA500\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"garlic-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Garlic is creamy white on the outside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Garlic is usually white or cream coloured!\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"garlic-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"garlic-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow underground in a bulb!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow underground as a bulb!\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am made of small pieces called cloves. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"garlic-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"garlic-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Each garlic bulb has lots of little cloves!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, garlic really is made of small pieces called cloves!\"},{\"id\":\"garlic-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT in the onion family?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"garlic-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Garlic\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Leek\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Chive\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"garlic-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"garlic-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Carrot is not in the onion family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Carrot is the odd one — it is not related to onions!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Ancient Egyptians worshipped garlic and placed it in the tombs of pharaohs!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"leek\",\"name\":\"Leek\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/leek.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"allium\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am the national symbol of Wales — go dragons!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Wales\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I look like a very big spring onion!\",\"highlightWord\":\"spring\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I have a milder, sweeter taste than an onion!\",\"highlightWord\":\"sweeter\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"My long green leaves fade to white at my base!\",\"highlightWord\":\"white\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"leek-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What two colours am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"leek-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFA500\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"leek-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am green on top and white at the bottom!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I am green at the top and white at my base!\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"leek-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"leek-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow upright in the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow in the ground above the soil line!\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am the national symbol of Wales. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"leek-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"leek-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Welsh people have used leeks as their symbol for centuries!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, the leek really is the national symbol of Wales!\"},{\"id\":\"leek-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT in the allium family?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"leek-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Leek\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Onion\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Garlic\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"leek-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Cucumber\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"leek-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Cucumber is a gourd, not an allium!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Cucumber is the odd one — it is not in the onion family!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Legend says Welsh soldiers wore leeks in their hats to tell friend from enemy in battle!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion\",\"name\":\"Spring Onion\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/spring-onion.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"allium\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"white\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"China\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am harvested young before my bulb gets big!\",\"highlightWord\":\"young\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"You can eat all of me — my white base and green top!\",\"highlightWord\":\"green\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in China thousands of years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"China\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I taste much milder and fresher than a big onion!\",\"highlightWord\":\"milder\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour are my long leaves?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spring-onion-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My long leaves are bright green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"My long leaves are green and my base is white!\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spring-onion-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow upright in the soil!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow upright in the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am just a young onion picked early. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spring-onion-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Spring onions are onions picked before they mature!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, spring onions really are young onions harvested early!\"},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT belong in the onion family?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Spring Onion\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Garlic\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Shallot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"spring-onion-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Courgette\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"spring-onion-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Courgette is a gourd, not in the onion family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Courgette is the odd one — it is a gourd, not an allium!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Spring onions can regrow from their white roots if you put them in a glass of water!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"courgette\",\"name\":\"Courgette\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/courgette.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"gourd\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"yellow\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"Mexico\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am actually a fruit, but people cook me as a veg!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fruit\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow very fast — I can double in size overnight!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fast\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"In America they call me a zucchini!\",\"highlightWord\":\"zucchini\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am usually dark green but can also be yellow!\",\"highlightWord\":\"yellow\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"courgette-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I usually?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"courgette-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"courgette-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Courgettes are usually dark green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Courgettes are usually dark green or sometimes yellow!\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"courgette-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"courgette-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on low spreading vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on vines close to the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"In America I am called a zucchini. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"courgette-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"courgette-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Same vegetable, different name across the Atlantic!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, Americans really do call me a zucchini!\"},{\"id\":\"courgette-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a gourd?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"courgette-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Courgette\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Pumpkin\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Cucumber\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"courgette-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Leek\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"courgette-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Leek is an allium, not a gourd!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Leek is the odd one — it is an allium, not a gourd!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"If left on the vine too long, a courgette can grow as big as a baseball bat!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin\",\"name\":\"Pumpkin\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/pumpkin.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"gourd\",\"colours\":[\"orange\",\"yellow\",\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"North America\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am 90% water even though I look so solid!\",\"highlightWord\":\"water\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"People carve me into lanterns for Halloween!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Halloween\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in North America thousands of years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"America\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I can grow to weigh over 1,000 kilograms!\",\"highlightWord\":\"1,000\",\"factType\":\"growth\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF6600\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pumpkin-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Pumpkins are bright orange!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Pumpkins are usually bright orange!\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pumpkin-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Pumpkins grow on long spreading vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Pumpkins actually grow on vines!\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I can be carved into a lantern. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pumpkin-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! People carve pumpkins into Jack-o-lanterns at Halloween!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, pumpkins really are carved into lanterns for Halloween!\"},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow on a vine?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Pumpkin\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Cucumber\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Butternut Squash\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pumpkin-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pumpkin-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Broccoli grows on a stalk, not a vine!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Broccoli is the odd one — it grows upright on a stalk!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"The world record pumpkin weighed over 1,200 kilograms — heavier than a small car!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash\",\"name\":\"Butternut Squash\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/butternut-squash.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"gourd\",\"colours\":[\"tan\",\"orange\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"Central America\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"My inside is a deep orange colour, full of goodness!\",\"highlightWord\":\"orange\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I am shaped like a pear with a long neck!\",\"highlightWord\":\"pear\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on long trailing vines in warm fields!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vines\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with vitamin A which helps your eyesight!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vitamin\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#D2B48C\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"butternut-squash-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My skin is a warm tan or beige colour!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"My skin is a pale tan or beige colour!\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"butternut-squash-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on long trailing vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on vines along the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am orange inside. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"butternut-squash-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My flesh inside is a deep orange colour!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, I am orange inside — that is where the goodness is!\"},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a type of squash?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Butternut Squash\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Acorn Squash\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Spaghetti Squash\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"butternut-squash-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Cauliflower\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"butternut-squash-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Cauliflower is a brassica, not a squash!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Cauliflower is the odd one — it is not a type of squash!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Butternut squash seeds can be toasted and eaten just like pumpkin seeds!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber\",\"name\":\"Cucumber\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/cucumber.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"gourd\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"India\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am 96% water — one of the most watery veggies!\",\"highlightWord\":\"water\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"I am actually a fruit, but eaten as a vegetable!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fruit\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in India over 3,000 years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"India\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am always cool and refreshing inside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cool\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"cucumber-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cucumber-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cucumber-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Cucumbers are green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Cucumbers are green on the outside!\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cucumber-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cucumber-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I climb and grow on vines!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on climbing vines!\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am actually a fruit. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cucumber-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cucumber-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Botanically I am a fruit because I have seeds inside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Surprise! Cucumbers are fruits because they contain seeds!\"},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT 90% or more water?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cucumber-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Cucumber\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Watermelon\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Lettuce\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cucumber-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Walnut\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cucumber-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Walnuts are dry and contain very little water!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Walnut is the odd one — it is mostly fat and protein, not water!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"The phrase \\\"cool as a cucumber\\\" is true — inside a cucumber can be 20°C cooler than the air outside!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli\",\"name\":\"Broccoli\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/broccoli.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Italy\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"My little green florets look like tiny trees!\",\"highlightWord\":\"trees\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with vitamin C and fibre!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vitamin\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"I was first grown in Italy over 2,000 years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Italy\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to cauliflower, cabbage and kale!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cauliflower\",\"factType\":\"family\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"broccoli-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broccoli-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broccoli-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Broccoli is bright green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Broccoli is green — like a little tree!\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broccoli-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broccoli-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on a thick stalk in the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow upright on a stalk in the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am related to cauliflower. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broccoli-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broccoli-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Broccoli and cauliflower are close cousins!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, broccoli and cauliflower really are closely related!\"},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT in the cabbage family?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"broccoli-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Cauliflower\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Kale\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"broccoli-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Sweetcorn\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"broccoli-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Sweetcorn is a grass, not in the cabbage family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Sweetcorn is the odd one — it is a grass, not a brassica!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Broccoli is one of the few vegetables that contains a complete protein!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower\",\"name\":\"Cauliflower\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/cauliflower.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"purple\",\"orange\",\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I can be white, purple, orange or even green!\",\"highlightWord\":\"purple\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"My white head is called a curd — like cheese!\",\"highlightWord\":\"curd\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am related to broccoli, cabbage and kale!\",\"highlightWord\":\"broccoli\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I originally came from the Mediterranean region!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mediterranean\",\"factType\":\"origin\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I most commonly?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#F5F5F5\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cauliflower-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Most cauliflowers are creamy white!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Cauliflowers are most often creamy white!\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cauliflower-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on a thick stalk in the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on a stalk above the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I can be purple or orange, not just white. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cauliflower-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Cauliflowers come in many colours!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, cauliflowers do come in purple and orange too!\"},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a brassica vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Cauliflower\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Brussels Sprout\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"cauliflower-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Courgette\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"cauliflower-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Courgette is a gourd, not a brassica!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Courgette is the odd one — it is a gourd, not a brassica!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"A cauliflower floret is actually an undeveloped flower — we eat it before it blooms!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn\",\"name\":\"Sweetcorn\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/sweetcorn.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"yellow\"],\"growsOn\":\"vine\",\"origin\":\"Mexico\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"Every ear of corn has an even number of rows!\",\"highlightWord\":\"even\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I grow on tall grass plants — yes, I am a grass!\",\"highlightWord\":\"grass\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in Mexico over 9,000 years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mexico\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"My bright yellow kernels are packed with energy!\",\"highlightWord\":\"yellow\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweetcorn-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Sweetcorn is golden yellow!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Sweetcorn is golden yellow!\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweetcorn-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on tall corn stalks like a vine plant!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on tall corn stalks — like a big grass plant!\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Every corn cob has an even number of rows. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweetcorn-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Corn cobs always have an even number of rows!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Amazing but true — corn cobs always have an even number of rows!\"},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT yellow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Sweetcorn\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Banana\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Lemon\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"sweetcorn-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"sweetcorn-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Broccoli is green, not yellow!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Broccoli is the odd one — it is green!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Sweetcorn is actually a cereal grain — the same family as wheat, rice and oats!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"pepper\",\"name\":\"Pepper\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/pepper.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"red\",\"yellow\",\"green\",\"orange\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"Central America\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"Red, yellow and green peppers are all the same pepper!\",\"highlightWord\":\"same\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I start green and turn red as I ripen!\",\"highlightWord\":\"ripen\",\"factType\":\"colour\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in Central America thousands of years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"America\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I have more vitamin C than an orange!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vitamin\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"pepper-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I when fully ripe?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pepper-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pepper-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Peppers turn bright red when fully ripe!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Peppers turn red when they are fully ripe!\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pepper-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pepper-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Peppers grow on bushy plants!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Peppers actually grow on bushy plants!\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Green and red peppers are the same pepper at different stages. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pepper-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pepper-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Green peppers are just unripe red peppers!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Surprise! Green peppers are the same as red — just picked earlier!\"},{\"id\":\"pepper-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a colour a pepper can be?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pepper-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Red\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Yellow\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Blue\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pepper-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Orange\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pepper-q4-c\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Peppers do not come in blue!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Blue is the odd one — peppers come in red, yellow, orange and green!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Red peppers have nearly three times more vitamin C than green peppers of the same size!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"tomato\",\"name\":\"Tomato\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/tomato.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"red\",\"yellow\",\"orange\",\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"South America\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am actually a fruit, not a vegetable!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fruit\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in the Andes mountains of South America!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Andes\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"There are over 10,000 varieties of me in the world!\",\"highlightWord\":\"10,000\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am packed with lycopene which keeps you healthy!\",\"highlightWord\":\"lycopene\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"tomato-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I when ripe?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"tomato-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF3333\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"tomato-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Most tomatoes are bright red when ripe!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Tomatoes are usually bright red when ripe!\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"tomato-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"tomato-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Tomatoes grow on bushy plants!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Tomatoes actually grow on bushy plants!\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am technically a fruit. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"tomato-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"tomato-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Tomatoes are fruits because they have seeds inside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, tomatoes are technically fruits — they have seeds!\"},{\"id\":\"tomato-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a fruit pretending to be a vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"tomato-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Tomato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Cucumber\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Pepper\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"tomato-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"tomato-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Carrot is a true vegetable — it is a root!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Carrot is the odd one — it is a true vegetable, not a fruit!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"In 1893 the US Supreme Court legally declared tomatoes to be vegetables for tax purposes!\",\"difficulty\":\"easy\"},{\"id\":\"avocado\",\"name\":\"Avocado\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/avocado.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"black\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"tree\",\"origin\":\"Mexico\",\"season\":\"all-year\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a fruit with a huge stone inside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"stone\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of healthy fats that are good for your brain!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fats\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in Mexico and Central America!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mexico\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"My creamy green flesh turns brown in the air!\",\"highlightWord\":\"brown\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"avocado-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my flesh inside?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"avocado-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#90EE90\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"avocado-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My inside is creamy pale green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"My flesh inside is a creamy pale green!\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"avocado-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q2-d\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"avocado-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on avocado trees in warm climates!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on trees in warm, tropical places!\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am technically a fruit with a big stone. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"avocado-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"avocado-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am a large berry with one massive seed inside!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, avocados are fruits — large berries with one big seed!\"},{\"id\":\"avocado-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow on a tree?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"avocado-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Avocado\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Mango\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Coconut\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"avocado-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Strawberry\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"avocado-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Strawberries grow on low plants on the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Strawberry is the odd one — it grows on the ground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"An avocado tree can live and produce fruit for over 400 years!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom\",\"name\":\"Mushroom\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/mushroom.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"brown\",\"white\",\"cream\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Worldwide\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am not a plant — I am a fungus!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fungus\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I spread by releasing tiny spores into the air!\",\"highlightWord\":\"spores\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am the only food that makes vitamin D from sunlight!\",\"highlightWord\":\"vitamin\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"},{\"text\":\"The largest living thing on Earth is a giant fungus!\",\"highlightWord\":\"largest\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"mushroom-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I most often?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"mushroom-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#8B4513\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#0000FF\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#32CD32\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"mushroom-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Mushrooms are usually brown or creamy white!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Mushrooms are usually brown or white!\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"mushroom-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q2-d\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"mushroom-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on the ground or on rotting wood!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on the ground or on dead wood!\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am a fungus, not a plant. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"mushroom-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"mushroom-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Mushrooms are fungi, not plants at all!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Surprise! Mushrooms are fungi — not plants!\"},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one IS a plant, not a fungus?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"mushroom-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Mushroom\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Toadstool\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Truffle\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"mushroom-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Broccoli\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"mushroom-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Broccoli is a real plant — not a fungus!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Broccoli is the odd one — it is a plant, while the others are fungi!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"A single mushroom can release up to 30,000 spores per second into the air!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine\",\"name\":\"Aubergine\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/aubergine.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"common\",\"colours\":[\"purple\",\"dark purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"bush\",\"origin\":\"India\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am actually a fruit — I have seeds inside!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fruit\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"In America they call me an eggplant!\",\"highlightWord\":\"eggplant\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in India over 4,000 years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"India\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"My beautiful dark purple skin is full of antioxidants!\",\"highlightWord\":\"purple\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"aubergine-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"aubergine-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4B0082\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#00FF00\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"aubergine-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Aubergines are a deep, rich purple!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Aubergines are a beautiful deep purple!\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"aubergine-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"aubergine-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on tall bushy plants!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on bushy plants!\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"Americans call me an eggplant. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"aubergine-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"aubergine-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Same vegetable, different name in the USA!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, Americans really do call me an eggplant!\"},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT purple?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"aubergine-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Aubergine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Red Cabbage\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Plum\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"aubergine-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Sweetcorn\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"aubergine-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Sweetcorn is yellow, not purple!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Sweetcorn is the odd one — it is yellow!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Aubergines belong to the nightshade family — the same as tomatoes, peppers and potatoes!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke\",\"name\":\"Artichoke\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/artichoke.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am actually the bud of a giant thistle flower!\",\"highlightWord\":\"thistle\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"You eat my thick petals by scraping them with your teeth!\",\"highlightWord\":\"petals\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew wild around the Mediterranean Sea!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mediterranean\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I make sweet things taste even sweeter after eating me!\",\"highlightWord\":\"sweeter\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"artichoke-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"artichoke-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#556B2F\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"artichoke-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Artichokes are a dark olive green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Artichokes are dark green, sometimes with purple tips!\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"artichoke-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"artichoke-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on tall thistle plants in the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on tall thistle-like plants!\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am the flower bud of a thistle plant. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"artichoke-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"artichoke-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am harvested before the thistle flower blooms!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, artichokes really are the buds of thistle flowers!\"},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT an exotic vegetable?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"artichoke-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Artichoke\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Asparagus\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Fennel\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"artichoke-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"artichoke-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Carrot is a very common vegetable!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Carrot is the odd one — it is a very common everyday vegetable!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"After eating an artichoke, water can taste sweeter — it contains a compound called cynarin!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus\",\"name\":\"Asparagus\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/asparagus.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"white\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"spring\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a spear that shoots up very fast in spring!\",\"highlightWord\":\"spear\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"A new asparagus plant takes three years to harvest!\",\"highlightWord\":\"three\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I make your wee smell funny — true fact!\",\"highlightWord\":\"wee\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I originally grew wild along the Mediterranean coasts!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mediterranean\",\"factType\":\"origin\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"asparagus-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I most often?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"asparagus-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFA500\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF69B4\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"asparagus-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Asparagus is usually green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Asparagus is usually green — sometimes white or purple!\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"asparagus-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q2-d\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"asparagus-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I shoot up from the ground like a spear!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually shoot straight up from the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I can grow 10 cm in just one day. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"asparagus-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"asparagus-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Asparagus spears can grow incredibly fast in spring!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, asparagus really can grow that fast in warm spring weather!\"},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow as a spear or stalk?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"asparagus-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Asparagus\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Celery\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Rhubarb\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"asparagus-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Pumpkin\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"asparagus-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! A pumpkin grows as a large round fruit, not a stalk!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Pumpkin is the odd one — it grows as a large round gourd!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"White asparagus is grown underground in darkness to stop it turning green from sunlight!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"fennel\",\"name\":\"Fennel\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/fennel.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"white\",\"pale green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Mediterranean\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I taste like liquorice — sweet and a little aniseedy!\",\"highlightWord\":\"liquorice\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"You can eat all of me — my bulb, stalks and feathery leaves!\",\"highlightWord\":\"bulb\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I originally grew in the Mediterranean region!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Mediterranean\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"My seeds are used as a spice in cooking around the world!\",\"highlightWord\":\"seeds\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"fennel-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my bulb?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"fennel-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#F5F5DC\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFA500\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"fennel-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My bulb is white or very pale green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"My bulb is pale white or light green!\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"fennel-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"fennel-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow upright in the ground with my bulb above the soil!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow upright with my bulb sitting above the soil!\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I taste like liquorice. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"fennel-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"fennel-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Fennel has a lovely sweet liquorice flavour!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, fennel really does taste like liquorice!\"},{\"id\":\"fennel-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT taste like liquorice or aniseed?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"fennel-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Fennel\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Star Anise\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Tarragon\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"fennel-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Carrot\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"fennel-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Carrots taste sweet and earthy, not like liquorice!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Carrot is the odd one — it tastes earthy and sweet, not like liquorice!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Ancient Greeks and Romans used fennel as a medicine, a food and even a symbol of victory!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"okra\",\"name\":\"Okra\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/okra.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"green\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"Africa\",\"season\":\"summer\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am also called ladies fingers because of my shape!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fingers\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I go sticky and gooey when cooked — that is normal!\",\"highlightWord\":\"sticky\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in northeast Africa thousands of years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Africa\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of fibre and vitamin C!\",\"highlightWord\":\"fibre\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"okra-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"okra-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"okra-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! Okra is bright green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Okra is bright green with a ridged pod!\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"okra-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q2-c\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"okra-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow on tall bushy plants above the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow on tall leafy plants above the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am also known as ladies fingers. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"okra-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"okra-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My long slim shape looks like fingers!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, okra really is called ladies fingers in many countries!\"},{\"id\":\"okra-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT come from Africa originally?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"okra-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Okra\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Watermelon\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Yam\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"okra-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Asparagus\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"okra-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Asparagus originally came from the Mediterranean!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Asparagus is the odd one — it came from the Mediterranean, not Africa!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Okra seeds can be roasted and ground to make a caffeine-free coffee substitute!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi\",\"name\":\"Pak Choi\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/pak-choi.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"green\",\"white\"],\"growsOn\":\"ground\",\"origin\":\"China\",\"season\":\"winter\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I am a type of Chinese cabbage with crunchy stalks!\",\"highlightWord\":\"cabbage\",\"factType\":\"family\"},{\"text\":\"My white stalks are juicy and my green leaves are tender!\",\"highlightWord\":\"juicy\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I have been grown in China for over 6,000 years!\",\"highlightWord\":\"6,000\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"I am full of calcium and vitamin K for strong bones!\",\"highlightWord\":\"calcium\",\"factType\":\"nutrition\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What two colours am I?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFA500\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#800080\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pak-choi-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I have green leaves and white stalks!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I have dark green leaves and crisp white stalks!\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q2-a\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q2-b\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On a vine\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌱\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pak-choi-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow as a leafy cluster above the ground!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow as a leafy cluster above the ground!\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am a type of cabbage. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pak-choi-q3-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! I am a Chinese cabbage in the brassica family!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, pak choi really is a type of Chinese cabbage!\"},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one is NOT a type of Asian leafy green?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Pak Choi\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Chinese Cabbage\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Bok Choy\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"pak-choi-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Artichoke\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"pak-choi-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Artichoke is Mediterranean, not an Asian leafy green!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Artichoke is the odd one — it is Mediterranean, not Asian!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"Pak choi is one of the most popular vegetables in Asia and is eaten almost every day in many Chinese households!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"},{\"id\":\"yam\",\"name\":\"Yam\",\"image\":\"/images/catalogue/yam.webp\",\"category\":\"vegetable\",\"subcategory\":\"exotic\",\"colours\":[\"brown\",\"white\",\"purple\"],\"growsOn\":\"underground\",\"origin\":\"Africa\",\"season\":\"autumn\",\"funFacts\":[{\"text\":\"I can grow to over one metre long underground!\",\"highlightWord\":\"metre\",\"factType\":\"growth\"},{\"text\":\"I am not the same as a sweet potato — I am different!\",\"highlightWord\":\"different\",\"factType\":\"surprise\"},{\"text\":\"I first grew in Africa and Asia thousands of years ago!\",\"highlightWord\":\"Africa\",\"factType\":\"origin\"},{\"text\":\"My skin is rough and dark like tree bark!\",\"highlightWord\":\"bark\",\"factType\":\"colour\"}],\"questions\":[{\"id\":\"yam-q1\",\"type\":\"colour-match\",\"questionText\":\"What colour is my skin?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"yam-q1-a\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#4A2800\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q1-b\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FF0000\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q1-c\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#228B22\",\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q1-d\",\"text\":null,\"colour\":\"#FFD700\",\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"yam-q1-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Yes! My rough outer skin is very dark brown!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"My skin is a very dark rough brown, like tree bark!\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q2\",\"type\":\"where-grow\",\"questionText\":\"Where do I grow?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"yam-q2-a\",\"text\":\"Underground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🕳️\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q2-b\",\"text\":\"On a tree\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌳\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q2-c\",\"text\":\"On a bush\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌿\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q2-d\",\"text\":\"On the ground\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":\"🌾\"}],\"correctOptionId\":\"yam-q2-a\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! I grow underground as a large starchy tuber!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"I actually grow underground as a big starchy tuber!\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q3\",\"type\":\"true-false\",\"questionText\":\"I am the same as a sweet potato. True or false?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"yam-q3-a\",\"text\":\"True\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q3-b\",\"text\":\"False\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"yam-q3-b\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Correct! Yams and sweet potatoes are completely different vegetables!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Actually, yams and sweet potatoes are completely different plants!\"},{\"id\":\"yam-q4\",\"type\":\"odd-one-out\",\"questionText\":\"Which one does NOT grow underground?\",\"options\":[{\"id\":\"yam-q4-a\",\"text\":\"Yam\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q4-b\",\"text\":\"Potato\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q4-c\",\"text\":\"Turnip\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null},{\"id\":\"yam-q4-d\",\"text\":\"Fennel\",\"colour\":null,\"icon\":null}],\"correctOptionId\":\"yam-q4-d\",\"explanationCorrect\":\"Right! Fennel grows above the ground with its bulb at the surface!\",\"explanationIncorrect\":\"Fennel is the odd one — its bulb sits at the soil surface, not underground!\"}],\"surpriseFact\":\"A single yam plant can produce tubers weighing up to 70 kilograms — heavier than a person!\",\"difficulty\":\"medium\"}],\"children\":\"$L3\"}]}]]}]]}],\"loading\":null,\"isPartial\":false}\n3:[\"$\",\"$L4\",null,{\"parallelRouterKey\":\"children\",\"template\":[\"$\",\"$L5\",null,{}],\"notFound\":[[[\"$\",\"title\",null,{\"children\":\"404: This page could not be found.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"style\":{\"fontFamily\":\"system-ui,\\\"Segoe UI\\\",Roboto,H